<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<chapter xml:id="ch-vector-spaces" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Vector Spaces</title>

<introduction>
<p>
  Learning goals:
  <ul>
    <li> Be able to verify that a subset of a vector space is or is NOT a subspace </li>
    <li> Find a spanning set for a subspace </li>
    <li> Be able to verify if a vector is in the span of other vectors </li>
    <li> Find a spanning set for the nullspace of a matrix </li>
    <li> Find a spanning set for the image space of matrix </li>
    <li> Be able to determine if a set of vectors is linearly independent via: a system of equations,
    the determinant of a matrix, or demonstrating a linear combination </li>
    <li> Know how span/linear independence connects to the invertibility criteria of matrices </li>
    <li> Know how to show a set is or is NOT a basis for a subspace </li>
    <li> Know how to find the dimension of a subspace </li>
    <li> Know how rank connects to dimension of row spaces/column spaces </li>
    <li> Know how to find a basis for the column space of a matrix (pick up the pivots!) </li>
    <li>If given one of the ten vector space properties, be able to verify if a property holds / does not hold for a potential vector space.</li>
    <li>Be able to produce counterexamples that show a set / operation is <em>not</em> a vector space, or provide counterexamples showing that a set / operation violates a property of vector spaces.</li>
  </ul>
</p>  
</introduction>

